caption: Fantastic movie, great story "Midnight in Paris",  this is the setting where he goes to find inspiration.

This is a place for fans of the movie "Midnight in Paris."  It's the place where the protagonist takes a taxi every night at midnight and is transported in time to the golden age of Paris.  It is still a nice place to visit and is a little off the beaten path and therefore more quiet.  You can also get some nice pictures.
Great place to visit. Lovely pictures and out of the way of the busy tourists.
Made Paris feel as magical as Gil makes it seem
It felt good to sit there and thinking about that great movie.
Great steps to hang out at around Midnight....
Yes, this is where Owen Wilson goes back in time in Midnight in Paris. A must-visit, it is located on the side stairs of this church behind the Pantheon.

Those who have seen the movie 'Midnight in Paris' cannot miss this place. Maybe it's been a while since the movie came out, but few people recognize this place as much as they used to. It was used as a key place for the protagonist to gain self-esteem and gain inspiration for his work.
The movie "Midnight in Paris" and everything is clear - this is the place from which to start a romantic walk
The square, the Church and the Panthéon are a group of buildings which share a location with the Sorbonne in Paris. They all offer a wonderful experience in and of themselves!!! 🫶🥳😍

This is where Gil, Owen Wilson's character in the film “Midnight in Paris”, waits for the car that transports him back in time to his explored Paris in the 1920s. An interesting place for those who enjoy the film.
